---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Advertising Policy"
  description="How we handle sponsorships, partnerships, and advertising while maintaining editorial independence."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Advertising Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/80">
        How we handle sponsorships and partnerships while maintaining editorial independence.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Our Approach to Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        PepCodex accepts limited sponsorships and partnerships to support our research
        and publishing operations. We maintain strict separation between editorial content
        and commercial relationships.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Accept</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Founding Partner sponsorships</strong> — Companies that support our mission
          with no editorial influence
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter sponsorships</strong> — Clearly labeled sponsored sections in
          our newsletter
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Educational partnerships</strong> — Collaborations with research institutions
          and medical education providers
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What We Don't Accept</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Advertising for peptide vendors or sources</li>
        <li>Sponsored content disguised as editorial</li>
        <li>Advertising that promotes specific dosing or protocols</li>
        <li>Pay-for-play coverage or reviews</li>
        <li>Advertising that contradicts our editorial standards</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclosure Standards</h2>
      <p>
        All sponsored content and partnerships are clearly disclosed:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sponsor logos appear only in designated sponsor sections</li>
        <li>Sponsored newsletter content is labeled "Sponsored"</li>
        <li>Partner pages are clearly identified as partner profiles</li>
        <li>We list all current sponsors on this page</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Editorial Firewall</h2>
      <p>
        Sponsors and partners have <strong>zero influence</strong> over our editorial content:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>They don't review content before publication</li>
        <li>They don't influence evidence grades or conclusions</li>
        <li>They don't determine which peptides we cover</li>
        <li>They can't request removal of unfavorable information</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Current Sponsors</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <p class="text-white/70 italic">
          We are currently accepting founding partners. If you're interested in supporting
          evidence-based peptide education, <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline">contact us about partnership opportunities</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our advertising policies or want to report a concern
        about a sponsorship, please contact us.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-white/60">
        Last updated: January 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
